for each displayed morphism { x } \xrightarrow [ f ]{ \bar{f} }{ y } in X over { b } \xrightarrow{f} { c } in B, an assigned morphism { \bar F _b{x} } \xrightarrow [ F {f} ]{ \bar F _f \bar{f} }{ \bar F _c y };
such that \bar F _{ 1 _{ b } } 1 _{ x } = 1 _{ \bar F _b x } and \bar F _{ f;g } { \left ( \bar{f} ; \bar{g} \right )} = \bar F _f{ \bar{f} }; \bar F _g{ \bar{g} }.When it does not cause confusion, we may drop some of the subscripts in our notation.

